Transcription.Text: For such pressures, however, it is necessary to limit telling span of the header tanks in order to avoid excessive periphal loadings in the plane of attachment to the block. Internal distributors are necessary to spread the flow and across the whole width of each passage, and these must be adequate to withstand the internal pressure loadings.
